festival.introText:
The iconic seafront festival returns to Brighton across two weekends this July.

Day Three sees industry heavyweight, Eric Prydz, top the line-up.

On The Beach announce the first line-up of our 2023 season: Sunday 23rd July sees the icon Eric Prydz step onto Brighton Beach.

Joined by a seriously heavy line-up featuring Adam Beyer, Kolsch, Cristoph and Eli & Fur - this is just the beginning of what they've got in store for you all this summer...

faqs.question: When is On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz?
faqs.answer: On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz takes place on Sunday the 23rd of July 2023.

faqs.question: Where is On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz?
faqs.answer: On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz is located on Brighton Beach.

faqs.question: Does On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes, you must be 18 years old or over to attend On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: Can I bring food & drink into On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Are PA tickets available for On The Beach 2023 - Day Three with Eric Prydz.
faqs.answer: Yes, please contact enquiries@louderuk.com to request a PA ticket.
